'''Civilians''' are citizens of [[West Ardougne]] who can be found in the western section of the city, just east of the [[Underground Pass (dungeon)|Underground Pass]]. When talked to, they will complain that they are busy because of the rat infestation, and say that they need a cat.

Players can sell [[cat|adult]], [[overgrown cat|overgrown]], [[wily cat|wily]] and [[lazy cat|lazy]] cats to civilians for 100 [[Death rune]]s each, or 200 after completing the [[Easy Ardougne Diary]]. This will have them take your cat away from you permanently, but you can buy a replacement from [[Gertrude]]. Note that they will not accept [[kitten]]s or the [[Witch's cat]] from the [[Underground Pass]]. To sell the cat you need to use it as an item on the Civilian.

